formatted_address: 1 HarbourFront Ave, Keppel Bay Tower, Singapore 098632
name: Dimbulah Coffee @ KBT

reviews.text: Decent coffee for Singapore. Had to throw in an extra shot into a small latte to get the coffee feels

Nice cozy little coffee shop for a quick chat or a business meeting. It's getting more popular now at certain times, so can be a bit noisy. The coffee is good and they have good food options. Generally easy to get a seat. It's tucked away at the back of the building.

I often have Iced latte there. Nice coffee and good service.
However, just realized from my colleague that they have loyalty card to collect stamp. Once you get the certain stamps, you will get a free coffee. However, My colleague had to ask them for that card. Otherwise, she would never get it. So would I!!

Busy coffee shop at bottom of Keppel Tower selling Australian grown coffee. I missed the lunch time rush but was still busy and it did look somewhat under staffed with only 2 employees working. Was limited food left when I arrived as all had been sold out. I did have the banana and walnut muffin which was heated in the microwave to the point of almost meltingâ€¦ if in the building again, I would probably just have a coffee.

Nice place Abit on tbe expensive side. The girls behind the counter are all Filipinos who serve the majority of the white trash with more happiness than locals. Food wise the  chicken mayo is nice. But overall ex.
